gomodel:SYNGO_4069  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 4A: Immunoelectron microscopy demonstrates AVP immunoreaction localised on DCV ( represented by white thin arrows) inside the axon terminals (AT) onto dendrites (dend) of a habenular neuron. Asterisks mark the docked DCVs containing AVP.\nFigure 4B: A postsynaptic dendritic shaft from CA3 pyramidal the neuron of ventral hippocampus receives a presynaptic innervation from a large diameter AT containing dense-core vesicles (dcv) that are AVP positive.\n\nThe paper does not comment on antibody specificity tests, however, it mentions that non-specific antibody binding was blocked with 20% NSS in TBS for 1 h after incubation with primary rabbit anti-AVP antibody. (PMID: 23085097). Experimental description: Adult male Wistar rats were used for immuno EM labelling of AVP in habenular neurons from the thalamus and CA3 pyramidal neurons from hippocampal slices." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2916-7616" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2020-12-08" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4069" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

